Corresponence Analysis

table_16_5 <- matrix(
  data = c(17, 17, 12,
           11,  9, 13,
           11,  8, 19,
           14,  7, 28),
  nrow = 4, byrow = TRUE,
  dimnames = list(1:4, 
                  c('n', 'c', 's')
                  )
)


(P <- table_16_5/sum(table_16_5))
##            n          c          s
## 1 0.10240964 0.10240964 0.07228916
## 2 0.06626506 0.05421687 0.07831325
## 3 0.06626506 0.04819277 0.11445783
## 4 0.08433735 0.04216867 0.16867470
(R <- solve(diag(rowSums(P))) %*% P)
##              n         c         s
## [1,] 0.3695652 0.3695652 0.2608696
## [2,] 0.3333333 0.2727273 0.3939394
## [3,] 0.2894737 0.2105263 0.5000000
## [4,] 0.2857143 0.1428571 0.5714286
(C <- P %*% solve(diag(colSums(P))))
##        [,1]      [,2]      [,3]
## 1 0.3207547 0.4146341 0.1666667
## 2 0.2075472 0.2195122 0.1805556
## 3 0.2075472 0.1951220 0.2638889
## 4 0.2641509 0.1707317 0.3888889
pipj <- outer(rowSums(P), colSums(P))
(chi_val <- sum((P - pipj)^2/pipj)*sum(table_16_5))
## [1] 11.72227
pchisq(chi_val, df = (nrow(P) - 1) * (ncol(P) - 1), lower.tail = F)
## [1] 0.06845936
d_inv_row <- chol(solve(diag(rowSums(P))))
d_inv_col <- chol(solve(diag(colSums(P))))

(Z <- d_inv_row %*% (P - pipj) %*% d_inv_col)
##             [,1]        [,2]        [,3]
## [1,]  0.04684964  0.12983653 -0.13817220
## [2,]  0.01109143  0.02309203 -0.02694171
## [3,] -0.02523597 -0.03510234  0.04814045
## [4,] -0.03227146 -0.11383750  0.11359145
Z_svd <- svd(Z)

all.equal(with(Z_svd, u %*% diag(d) %*% t(v)), Z)
## [1] TRUE
A <- sqrt(diag(rowSums(P))) %*% Z_svd$u
B <- sqrt(diag(colSums(P))) %*% Z_svd$v

X <- solve(diag(rowSums(P))) %*% A %*% diag(Z_svd$d)
Y <- solve(diag(colSums(P))) %*% B %*% diag(Z_svd$d)


sum(Z_svd$d[1:2]^2)/sum(Z_svd$d^2)
## [1] 1
rownames(X) <- rownames(table_16_5)
rownames(Y) <- colnames(table_16_5)

bind_rows(as_tibble(X, rownames = "lab"), as_tibble(Y, rownames = "lab")) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = V1, y = V2, label = lab)) + geom_text() +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(-.2, .2))
